Abstract = {Six species of Burmeistera H. Karst. \& Triana are described as new from
   Ecuador: B. chrysothrix Mashburn \& Muchhala, B. crocodila Mashburn \&
   Muchhala, B. erosa Mashburn, B. lingulata Mashburn \& Muchhala, B.
   sierrazulensis Mashburn \& Muchhala, and B. valdiviana Mashburn. These
   discoveries bring the total number of Burmeistera species in Ecuador to
   ca. 47. Descriptions are given for each species, as well as diagnoses to
